Frank HUNTER v. Fred B. ZERBST, Warden of the United States Penitentiary at Leavenworth, Kansas. No. 1097. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. May 17, 1934. Luther Burns, of .Topeka, Kan., for appellant. S. S. Alexander, U. S. Atty., of Topeka, Kan., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for want of merit.
